our change() on ArticleDialogBox can be so big
(if number of UIController get increase)
we can fix this by implementing MEDIATOR pattern by OBSERVER pattern!


Cenna:
we can delete the DialogBox class as mediator (we don't need change() method anymore)
we want to update ArticleDialogBox (the form,the dialog box!)
if any of the source obj (like button, listBox, TextBox,...) get change
so all UIController obj is source (we make UIController as source (as subject))
and we want to update the dialogBox (ArticleDialogBox is our observer)

problem: I make ArticleDialogBox as observer (implement observer interface)
         and each UIController as source (multiple source)
         I attach ArticleDialogBox on each source notifier. (so if each one has changed
                                                             ArticleDialogBox get notified)
         but when we want to Override update method (from observer interface)
         we need put some if/else to separate these source and make compatible update
         so it's gonna be same as "change" method (we have no improvement!)


Mosh: Mosh solve this problem, by "EVENT BASE" approach
      he said, when a source has change actually
      we don't want to notify whole ArticleDialogBox obj
      we just want to notify some method of ArticleDialogBox (like articleSelected/titleChanged)
      so instead adding ArticleDialogBox obj as observer to the source
      we add exact method as observer to the source  (if ListBox (ArticleListBox) has change
                                                      we want to execute articleSelected() of mediator:
                                                      ** articlesListBox.attach(()->articleSelected()); **
                                                      )


summary: by making an method (event) as observer (instead of whole mediator obj)
         we can remove conditions to separate event on mediator
         it's what we call EVENT HANDLER"
         in many GUI framework use this concept
         (observer interface has the name of "EventHandler")









